===============================================================================
Third-party components
===============================================================================

xff links the libraries below, fetched via Bazel modules. All are under
permissive licenses (no copyleft); the notice-retention obligation is satisfied
by reproducing each project's name and license identifier here. Run
`xff --help=licenses` for a summary of what a given binary actually contains.

Core (always linked):

  Abseil (C++)   Apache-2.0     https://github.com/abseil/abseil-cpp
  RE2            BSD-3-Clause   https://github.com/google/re2
  helly25/mbo    Apache-2.0     https://github.com/helly25/mbo

Build-time extras -- linked ONLY when the matching `--//xff:<extra>` Bazel flag
is set, and therefore ABSENT from the default (lean) binary. The notice set
scales with the enabled extras:

  archive  (--//xff:archive), via libarchive:
    libarchive     BSD-2-Clause
    zlib           Zlib
    bzip2          bzip2-1.0.6
    xz / liblzma   0BSD           (public-domain-equivalent; no notice required)
    zstd           BSD-3-Clause   (dual-licensed; the BSD arm is used, never GPL-2.0)
    lz4            BSD-2-Clause   (the library; never the GPL-2.0 command-line tool)
    (mbedtls, for encrypted-archive reading, is deliberately NOT linked.)

  regex  (--//xff:pcre), via PCRE2:
    PCRE2          BSD-3-Clause
